cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with learning a hidden hypergraph, which is a problem in both machine learning and theoretical computer science. The algorithmic aspect of the problem suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of queries to learn the hypergraph suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the focus on learning a hidden structure suggests that it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
